text:
  We address potential impacts of climate change as part of our risk model, which draws on risk-based capital concepts  In the model, risks are classified into four main categories:
	Investment risks;
	Pricing risks, including determination of adequate spreads or premiums, and estimation of claims, both expected and catastrophic;
	Interest rate risk, including asset/liability duration matching exposures;
	Other business risks, including business continuity, data security, and other operational risks
The potential impact of climate change, such as hurricanes or natural disasters, is addressed in this model by reviewing geographic concentration in our investment and pricing risk assessments

